  "stem": "<p>The graph of <i>y</i> = 3<i>x</i>&sup2; + <i>bx</i> + <i>c</i> is a parabola that opens upward with vertex at (&minus;2, &minus;5). The parabola passes through the points (&minus;3, &minus;2), (&minus;2, &minus;5), and (&minus;1, &minus;2). What is the value of <i>c</i>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "7"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>The vertex form is <i>y</i> = 3(<i>x</i> + 2)&sup2; &minus; 5. Expanding: <i>y</i> = 3(<i>x</i>&sup2; + 4<i>x</i> + 4) &minus; 5 = 3<i>x</i>&sup2; + 12<i>x</i> + 12 &minus; 5 = 3<i>x</i>&sup2; + 12<i>x</i> + 7. So <i>c</i> = 7.</p>",
